Malcolm Ross Kinsella Ryan wrote:
>
>> ======================================================================
>> Text of Adopted Proposals
>> ======================================================================
>> Proposal 3809 (Gen Chaos) AI = 1
>> Ten Days is Too Long
>> 
>> Be it therefore resolved, that Rule 693 be amended, by replacing "ten
>> days "with "seven days".
>> 
>> ======================================================================
>
>Now here's a pretty pickle. Proposals 3810-12 were distributed last 
>Monday. When does their voting period end? Is it seven days after it
>began, or is it ten? If it's seven, then it is already over. If it is
>ten, then there is still time for me to vote:
>
>I vote FOR 3810, AGAINST 3811, and ABTAIN on 3812. So there.

I think this is fine. The most natural way to think of Voting Periods is
as an attribute of Proposals which is fixed at the time they are
distributed. If we think of them in this way, then changing the VPs of
Proposals already distributed becomes a retroactive application of the
amendment to R693.

(One might argue that the application need not be retroactive: we might
think of the effect of the amendment as changing, in the present, the
value of the Proposals' attribute "length-of-VP". But at least in this
case, that argument won't quite work, since the effect will be to make
it the case, in the present, that the VPs ended a few days ago - and
that is a change in the past.)

